1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,984
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,051 --> 00:00:21,588
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,654 --> 00:00:23,757
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:23,823 --> 00:00:27,060
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:28,294 --> 00:00:30,063
LET'S HAVE ANOTHER GOOD ONE

6
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:31,831
Chef Eun-yeong.

7
00:00:31,898 --> 00:00:34,534
We should begin by congratulating you.
Please give her a big hand.

8
00:00:34,934 --> 00:00:36,903
CONGRATULATIONS

9
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:40,140
As of this shoot, she has yet to marry.

10
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:41,641
But by the time this goes on air,

11
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:43,877
-she would've been married for a week.
-That's right.

12
00:00:43,943 --> 00:00:45,245
-That's the case.
-She must be over the moon.

13
00:00:45,311 --> 00:00:48,314
You'll probably get to watch this
while you're on your honeymoon.

14
00:00:48,381 --> 00:00:49,783
-Are you traveling far?
-To Hawaii.

15
00:00:49,849 --> 00:00:51,785
-"You go to Hawaii."
-Nice.

16
00:00:51,851 --> 00:00:54,654
Not only am I curious to see
Eun-yeong's wedding,

17
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:55,989
but Hyun-suk's wedding song…

18
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:59,626
-So you decided to do it?
-You're pushing ahead with it?

19
00:00:59,692 --> 00:01:02,262
-I believe many tried to stop him.
-I didn't have a choice.

20
00:01:02,328 --> 00:01:03,897
She couldn't reason against him.

21
00:01:03,963 --> 00:01:05,298
Of course, we filmed it.

22
00:01:05,365 --> 00:01:07,901
Let's watch Eun-yeong's wedding together.

23
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:10,703
Hello, I'm Yoon Nam-no,
reporting for <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

24
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:13,940
I'm standing in front
of Chef Eun-yeong's bridal suite.

25
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:15,842
-Hello, Sung-ju.
-Hi.

26
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,577
You sound really awkward.

27
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:19,279
THE ROOKIE CORRESPONDENT

28
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:20,980
Hello. Congratulations, Chef Eun-yeong.

29
00:01:21,047 --> 00:01:21,881
FINALLY MEETING THE BRIDE

30
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:24,350
-Thank you.
-Representing the hosts and the chefs.

31
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:26,853
TAKING A PHOTO TO REMEMBER

32
00:01:27,087 --> 00:01:29,556
JONG-WON ATTENDED TOO

33
00:01:29,622 --> 00:01:30,690
Thank you.

34
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:33,660
-Can you leave her a message?
-A congratulatory message?

35
00:01:33,726 --> 00:01:37,597
Chef Hyun-suk
is extremely nervous at the moment.

36
00:01:37,664 --> 00:01:38,731
PEACE

37
00:01:38,798 --> 00:01:42,268
-He picked out a song by Bruno Mars.
-Bruno Mars?

38
00:01:42,335 --> 00:01:44,070
Bruno Mars won't be coming, though.

39
00:01:44,137 --> 00:01:45,472
Instead, Bruised Mars is coming.

40
00:01:45,672 --> 00:01:47,073
A LAME JOKE…

41
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:50,310
Let us meet the couple of the day.

42
00:01:51,344 --> 00:01:53,880
-Let the bride…
-I'll film it.

43
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:54,981
…enter.

44
00:01:55,548 --> 00:01:57,484
ANTICIPATION

45
00:01:58,318 --> 00:02:00,987
THE STAR OF THE DAY FINALLY SHOWS HERSELF

46
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,858
I want to get married too.

47
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:06,759
She's gorgeous.

48
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:10,263
THE CHEF & MY FRIDGE FAMILY
WATCH HER AFFECTIONATELY

49
00:02:12,365 --> 00:02:13,600
Looking gorgeous!

50
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:14,801
CHOKING UP…

51
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:17,170
THE BRIDE MEETS HER GROOM

52
00:02:17,237 --> 00:02:20,206
And now, we have the wedding singers
who will sing

53
00:02:20,273 --> 00:02:22,275
-for the bride and the groom.
-The wedding song.

54
00:02:22,342 --> 00:02:24,644
Please welcome Mr. Choi Hyun-suk
for the first song.

55
00:02:24,711 --> 00:02:26,980
ARMS CROSSED

56
00:02:27,046 --> 00:02:28,882
Before I sing, I'd like to make

57
00:02:28,948 --> 00:02:30,917
a few announcements
to the distinguished guests.

58
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,386
I did not force her to let me sing.

59
00:02:33,586 --> 00:02:34,888
BOO

60
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:37,290
-She was not forced into it.
-Why is he saying that here?

61
00:02:37,357 --> 00:02:39,792
Whenever I sing at weddings,
the vibe always gets better,

62
00:02:39,859 --> 00:02:41,461
and people tend to request an encore.

63
00:02:41,528 --> 00:02:43,229
So for today,

64
00:02:43,296 --> 00:02:44,964
I prepared an encore too.

65
00:02:45,231 --> 00:02:46,499
NO DEMAND BUT SUPPLIED

66
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:47,967
SHAKING HEAD…

67
00:02:48,034 --> 00:02:49,469
-For the encore song…
-But I'm hungry.

68
00:02:49,769 --> 00:02:52,238
THE FINAL ORDER OF THE WEDDING FOLLOWED

69
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:55,708
THE BRIDE AND GROOM'S PROCESSION

70
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:56,976
NAM-NO, JONG-WON

71
00:02:57,043 --> 00:03:00,413
ENDING WITH A FLOWER SHOWER!

72
00:03:00,713 --> 00:03:03,950
WE WISH YOU A LIFETIME OF HAPPINESS,
OUR DEAR EUN-YEONG

73
00:03:04,984 --> 00:03:08,154
WE WHOLEHEARTEDLY CONGRATULATE
CHEF EUN-YEONG ON HER MARRIAGE

74
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:11,291
THE LEAD ROLES OF THE WEDDING

75
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:14,427
Your voice cracked
during the song. Come on.

76
00:03:14,494 --> 00:03:15,528
HIS PREDICTION CAME TRUE

77
00:03:15,595 --> 00:03:16,963
The hall was rather big,

78
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,732
-but his voice filled it up.
-He has a loud voice.

79
00:03:19,799 --> 00:03:20,967
Since I'm at that level,

80
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,535
should I release a song?

81
00:03:22,802 --> 00:03:23,836
EXPLODING WITH CONFIDENCE

82
00:03:23,903 --> 00:03:25,004
Do not do it.

83
00:03:25,071 --> 00:03:26,539
-Don't push ahead.
-Don't force it.

84
00:03:26,606 --> 00:03:27,874
HMM…

85
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:29,108
If you keep making me angry,

86
00:03:29,175 --> 00:03:30,176
I will release a song!

87
00:03:30,410 --> 00:03:32,045
THREATENING WITH A SONG RELEASE

88
00:03:33,613 --> 00:03:35,248
Anyway, Chef Eun-yeong.

89
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:38,451
-We wish you a happy married life.
-Thank you.

90
00:03:38,518 --> 00:03:39,586
Congratulations.

91
00:03:39,652 --> 00:03:43,156
We're now going to welcome
the fridge owners

92
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,625
who'll join us today.

93
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:48,895
We present the fridge owners.
Please come on out!

94
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,866
Today's fridge owners!

95
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:56,169
Please welcome
Shin Ye-eun and Lee Jun-young!

96
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,804
-Welcome to the show.
-Welcome.

97
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:00,240
-Please greet the viewers.
-This is so great.

98
00:04:00,306 --> 00:04:01,741
Please, take a seat.

99
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:03,476
He's so cool and good-looking.

100
00:04:03,543 --> 00:04:04,911
-Hello.
-Please take a seat.

101
00:04:04,978 --> 00:04:07,046
Let me introduce you
to the guest next to me.

102
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:09,315
"What took you so long?"

103
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:10,917
"I missed you to death."

104
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:14,988
It sounds gross when you say it.

105
00:04:15,054 --> 00:04:16,689
"I missed you to death."

106
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:19,025
<i>She starred in </i>The Glory
<i>as the cruelest villain,</i>

107
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:21,728
but in reality,
she's a lovely bright-eyed maniac.

108
00:04:21,794 --> 00:04:23,563
Please welcome actor Shin Ye-eun!

109
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,632
-It's nice to see you.
-It's great to be here.

110
00:04:25,698 --> 00:04:26,799
LOVELY

111
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,101
CAN'T EVEN LOOK AT HER

112
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:29,202
Let me introduce him.

113
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:30,703
Is this the right dance?

114
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:33,906
-"Am I that…" Is this it?
-Yes, that's right.

115
00:04:33,973 --> 00:04:35,041
-You know, right?
-Yes.

116
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:37,210
-Of course. This is it.
-Is this how you do it?

117
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,645
-This dance.
-It's this dance.

118
00:04:38,711 --> 00:04:40,246
Your hands need to be in your pockets.

119
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:41,981
This is just an old dude's dance.

120
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:43,349
ADD THE THUMBS TO MAKE IT OLD

121
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:45,652
See? It becomes an old man's dance.

122
00:04:45,718 --> 00:04:47,520
<i>He made his debut</i>
<i>as a member of U-KISS.</i>

123
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:49,656
<i>He starred in</i> D.P., Weak Hero Class 2,

124
00:04:49,722 --> 00:04:51,624
<i>played the villain in</i> Mask Girl,

125
00:04:51,691 --> 00:04:53,826
<i>and played Yeong-bum</i>
<i>in</i> When Life Gives You Tangerines.

126
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:57,130
The son of Netflix
who isn't easily pushed around,

127
00:04:57,196 --> 00:05:00,600
-please welcome actor Lee Jun-young!
-Lee Jun-young.

128
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,201
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

129
00:05:02,435 --> 00:05:03,269
BOWS

130
00:05:03,336 --> 00:05:05,038
Hello. I'm Lee Jun-young.

131
00:05:05,104 --> 00:05:06,939
It's nice to see you.
You're one handsome man.

132
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,641
BUSY HANDS

133
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:10,410
You seem a bit shy.

134
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:13,346
-I'm really shy.
-You are?

135
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:16,082
-I see.
-Your ears look like they can be drained.

136
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:16,983
GOSH…

137
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,085
He's wriggling and fidgeting.

138
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:22,622
-Straighten your back. It's okay.
-Yes, it's fine.

139
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:23,990
-You're the guest.
-Okay.

140
00:05:24,057 --> 00:05:27,093
Ye-eun wrote down Kim Poong as the chef

141
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,762
-she wants to meet the most.
-What? I'm not a chef.

142
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:32,065
When I cook…

143
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:34,200
I'm not saying he's like this,

144
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:37,437
but when I cook, the process

145
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,373
may not look too great, but the result

146
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:43,209
-turns out nicely.
-You have the right idea about me.

147
00:05:43,276 --> 00:05:45,678
She's saying you two have a similar style…

148
00:05:45,745 --> 00:05:46,746
-That's right.
-…when you cook.

149
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:48,381
Thank you.

150
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:51,651
It looks like Sung-jun was hopeful.
He doesn't seem too happy about this.

151
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:53,986
-Me?
-Did you get hopeful?

152
00:05:54,053 --> 00:05:55,555
-No.
-It's written on your face.

153
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:57,857
-He even lost weight recently.
-It's not that.

154
00:05:57,924 --> 00:05:59,726
I rarely watch dramas,

155
00:05:59,792 --> 00:06:03,129
-but I never miss anything she stars in.
-Whoa!

156
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:06,432
It's my first time
seeing Sung-jun so flushed.

157
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:08,568
-Really?
-Your ears are so red.

158
00:06:08,634 --> 00:06:09,969
-Your ears are really red.
-Hey.

159
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,304
Poke it and let the blood out.

160
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,506
It sounds like
he's a huge fan of Ye-eun's.

161
00:06:13,573 --> 00:06:15,908
Jun-young, you have some updates.

162
00:06:15,975 --> 00:06:17,643
My new project

163
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,480
will premiere on May 30th.

164
00:06:20,546 --> 00:06:24,617
-It's called <i>Reborn Rookie.</i>
<i>-Reborn Rookie.</i>

165
00:06:24,684 --> 00:06:26,219
A rookie who's reborn?

166
00:06:26,285 --> 00:06:30,056
-Son Hyun-joo and I switch souls.
-Your souls change?

167
00:06:30,123 --> 00:06:32,458
Due to an unexpected accident,

168
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:34,727
<i>he gets to live his second life.</i>

169
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:36,462
Why am I that punk?

170
00:06:37,096 --> 00:06:39,365
A CHAIRMAN WHO LOST EVERYTHING

171
00:06:39,832 --> 00:06:41,534
RETURNS AS A ROOKIE TO TURN IT ALL AROUND

172
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:44,370
That's the plot of the show.

173
00:06:44,437 --> 00:06:46,205
Right after our show,

174
00:06:46,272 --> 00:06:50,443
-<i>Reborn Rookie</i> will be aired.
-You can watch them back-to-back.

175
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:53,980
Ye-eun, I believe
you also were in a drama production.

176
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:56,048
Yes! My drama

177
00:06:56,115 --> 00:06:58,484
is called <i>Doctor on the Edge.</i>

178
00:06:58,551 --> 00:07:01,521
A nurse and a public health doctor
who's serving their military duty

179
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:08,127
go to an island to treat and heal people
as many different episodes unfold.

180
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:09,362
TUNE INTO HER DRAMA TOO

181
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:12,432
Ye-eun is famous for her performance

182
00:07:12,498 --> 00:07:17,136
in the drama <i>The Glory</i>
when she played teen Yeon-jin.

183
00:07:17,203 --> 00:07:20,873
One of us became very scared
after hearing you'd be on the show.

184
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:21,774
Who is it?

185
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:24,210
It's Jun-young.

186
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:25,778
That's why he's trembling.

187
00:07:26,045 --> 00:07:28,014
THE REASON WAS FINALLY REVEALED

188
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,216
-It wasn't us!
-It wasn't!

189
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,451
I was wondering why.

190
00:07:31,517 --> 00:07:33,553
Have you two ever worked together?

191
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:35,621
-It's our first time.
-It is? Today?

192
00:07:35,688 --> 00:07:36,923
He kept looking at the ground.

193
00:07:36,989 --> 00:07:40,059
No, it's not that. But I think she has

194
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:41,894
great eyes for a variety of productions.

195
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:44,363
-Her eyes?
-They're perfect

196
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:47,233
to play either the villain
or the good character.

197
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,168
She has such bright eyes.

198
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:51,471
I also thought

199
00:07:51,537 --> 00:07:56,375
he has the perfect features
to play someone wicked or good.

200
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:57,643
AGREED

201
00:07:57,710 --> 00:08:01,380
What do you mean by the eyes
that can look either wicked or good?

202
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:02,715
When you play a villain,

203
00:08:02,782 --> 00:08:06,819
it's more advantageous
if you can show more of the whites.

204
00:08:07,386 --> 00:08:08,921
LIKE THIS?

205
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:09,956
Like scleral show?

206
00:08:10,022 --> 00:08:11,424
Can you control the size of your pupils?

207
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:13,526
I wouldn't call it that,
but it's the position.

208
00:08:13,593 --> 00:08:14,794
-The position.
-The position.

209
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:16,295
CURIOUS

210
00:08:16,362 --> 00:08:18,664
-First, it's like this.
-Yes. The good eyes.

211
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:20,566
For example…

212
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:22,735
PUTTING ON THE VILLAIN EYES

213
00:08:22,802 --> 00:08:24,537
-Whoa.
-That's cool. How do you do that?

214
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:26,372
I'm showing more of my whites.

215
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:28,908
-Yes, you seem like a maniac.
-The vibe changes.

216
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:30,243
That's scary.

217
00:08:30,309 --> 00:08:32,311
He has those eyes.

218
00:08:32,378 --> 00:08:34,514
I think there's such a difference.

219
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:36,449
LIKE THIS?

220
00:08:36,515 --> 00:08:37,850
Can you show us?

221
00:08:37,917 --> 00:08:40,253
Jun-young just said you had those eyes.

222
00:08:40,319 --> 00:08:43,155
Why did you show that to them?
This is too much pressure!

223
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,458
SORRY, DID NOT INTEND THAT…

224
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,593
I think <i>Reborn Rookie</i> is going to do well.

225
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:49,662
-Me too.
-Do it for <i>Doctor on the Edge.</i>

226
00:08:49,729 --> 00:08:50,796
For <i>Doctor on the Edge.</i>

227
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:53,032
-Where do I look?
-Who wants to be stared at?

228
00:08:53,099 --> 00:08:54,333
-I'm scared.
-Sung-jun?

229
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,234
ME!

230
00:08:55,301 --> 00:08:58,070
Do it to Sung-jun. Say the line,

231
00:08:58,137 --> 00:09:00,072
"I missed you to death."

232
00:09:00,139 --> 00:09:01,707
So he's Dong-eun?

233
00:09:01,774 --> 00:09:03,843
-Let's do that.
-Sounds great.

234
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,848
COLD STARE…

235
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:10,917
KWON DONG-EUN IS ALREADY SCARED

236
00:09:10,983 --> 00:09:12,285
DONG-EUN'S FRIEND IS ALSO SCARED

237
00:09:12,351 --> 00:09:14,420
What took you so long?

238
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:18,190
I missed you to death.

239
00:09:18,257 --> 00:09:20,259
-He was already not looking.
-Look at him.

240
00:09:20,493 --> 00:09:21,594
SUNG-JUN, ARE YOU CRYING?

241
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:24,730
-His eyes are trembling.
-He wasn't late, but it feels like he was.

242
00:09:24,797 --> 00:09:26,632
YEON-JIN, I'M REALLY SCARED RIGHT NOW…

243
00:09:26,699 --> 00:09:28,301
-That's so scary.
-Sung-jun.

244
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:29,235
How did that feel?

245
00:09:29,302 --> 00:09:31,203
I'm glad I came today. That was great.

246
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,005
Aren't you always here?

247
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:33,973
You're a cast member.

248
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,541
HAHAHA…

249
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:37,176
CHUCKLING…

250
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:39,245
Please remember us

251
00:09:39,312 --> 00:09:42,648
and give us some credit if you two
get to work together in the future.

252
00:09:42,715 --> 00:09:44,317
THEIR CHEMISTRY IS PROMISING

253
00:09:44,383 --> 00:09:46,619
-Straighten your back.
-Yes.

254
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:48,020
You're a cool guy.

255
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:49,121
BOWING(?)

256
00:09:49,188 --> 00:09:51,624
How many times are you bowing to her?

257
00:09:53,859 --> 00:09:56,362
-It's almost like a ritual.
-How many times?

258
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:58,664
You can't do that too many times.

259
00:09:58,731 --> 00:09:59,832
Just greet her once.

260
00:09:59,899 --> 00:10:02,468
He's a funny one, isn't he?

261
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:05,204
HE HAS THAT CHOI KANG-ROK VIBE…

262
00:10:06,238 --> 00:10:08,741
Chef Jong-won said one of our chefs

263
00:10:08,808 --> 00:10:12,345
-would make a great villain.
-What? Who?

264
00:10:12,411 --> 00:10:13,913
There's someone who's usually kind,

265
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:15,748
but also can change in an instant.

266
00:10:15,815 --> 00:10:17,483
-Who can be a villain?
-Chef Eun-yeong.

267
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:19,485
-Eun-yeong.
-Me?

268
00:10:19,552 --> 00:10:21,454
-She's charismatic too.
-Do I seem like that?

269
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:24,056
-At times, she seems emotionless.
-Does she?

270
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:25,091
When she dances.

271
00:10:25,424 --> 00:10:27,727
DEAD-EYES MODE

272
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,261
She smiles like that, then suddenly,

273
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:30,396
makes a straight face.

274
00:10:30,896 --> 00:10:32,965
LIKE THIS?

275
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:35,735
-Stop it!
-She's doing it again.

276
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,203
YOU REALLY DO SCARE US…

277
00:10:37,269 --> 00:10:39,005
She's like the Hong Kong Granny Ghost.

278
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,306
DEAD-EYED HONG KONG GHOST

279
00:10:40,373 --> 00:10:42,441
KIND NEWLYWED BRIDE

280
00:10:42,508 --> 00:10:46,412
-What do you think, Ye-eun?
-Your eyes change completely.

281
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,115
My eyes suddenly change whenever I dance.

282
00:10:49,181 --> 00:10:50,583
I already knew about that.

283
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,084
Thanks, I watched you a lot too.

284
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:58,090
Both of you have played villains,

285
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:01,994
so who would you cast
if you were the director? Ye-eun?

286
00:11:02,061 --> 00:11:03,062
Chef Jong-won.

287
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:06,432
-Chef Jong-won.
-Can he also be a villain?

288
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:08,367
He seems like someone who's only good,

289
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:10,202
but in the back,

290
00:11:10,269 --> 00:11:12,505
he could actually be
the boss behind everything.

291
00:11:12,571 --> 00:11:13,606
Chef Jong-won.

292
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:16,742
Can you act out a scene
where you taste blood?

293
00:11:16,809 --> 00:11:19,412
S#1. TASTING BLOOD WITH HIS FINGER

294
00:11:19,478 --> 00:11:20,780
And then, open your eyes.

295
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,281
-That's too far.
-Right?

296
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,216
-First, taste the blood.
-Taste it.

297
00:11:24,283 --> 00:11:26,752
-Then open your eyes.
-Your eyes.

298
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:28,254
-How do you do it?
-Tasting blood.

299
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,422
A BRIEF ACTING LESSON

300
00:11:29,488 --> 00:11:30,956
He's practicing acting.

301
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:31,891
I was asking Eun-yeong.

302
00:11:32,324 --> 00:11:33,793
THE GAZE EXPERT DEMONSTRATES

303
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:34,760
Taste it and…

304
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:40,299
SHOCK AND TERROR…

305
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:43,502
-That's so scary!
-That's horrifying!

306
00:11:43,569 --> 00:11:45,971
Like the Annabelle doll!

307
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:49,141
A SCENE YOU DO NOT WANT AT HOME

308
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:50,042
The Annabelle doll.

309
00:11:50,109 --> 00:11:52,111
Taste the blood, then the gaze.

310
00:11:58,751 --> 00:11:59,585
GETTING CHILLS

311
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:02,088
-He has that look.
-That was scary.

312
00:12:02,154 --> 00:12:03,889
You have to be good-looking to be scary.

313
00:12:04,356 --> 00:12:05,191
WHOA…

314
00:12:05,257 --> 00:12:06,092
AWESOME JOB

315
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:08,294
-It wasn't seasoned right.
-We got one.

316
00:12:08,694 --> 00:12:10,629
HE NEEDED A WHOLE WEEK
TO RECOVER FROM THIS…

317
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:14,667
Ye-eun is actually
someone very playful and cute.

318
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,469
At the Busan International Film Festival,

319
00:12:16,535 --> 00:12:20,172
she earned the title of Cuteness MVP.

320
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:21,607
<i>Thanks to her,</i>

321
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:24,043
the air at the film festival
changed completely.

322
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:26,078
-We prepared a clip.
-Really?

323
00:12:26,145 --> 00:12:27,847
So let's take a look.

324
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:30,883
THE 30TH BIFF OPENING RED CARPET EVENT

325
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:32,118
<i>The opening red carpet event.</i>

326
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:33,719
DID THE PHOTO WALL WITH CHARISMA

327
00:12:34,286 --> 00:12:36,455
<i>The air there is quite solemn.</i>

328
00:12:36,522 --> 00:12:37,389
What's she doing?

329
00:12:38,557 --> 00:12:40,893
CUTE WALKING
THAT MAKES EVERYONE WHO SEES HER HAPPY

330
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,361
BLUSH

331
00:12:42,828 --> 00:12:45,631
-Look at the other two.
-She walked like this.

332
00:12:45,698 --> 00:12:47,733
People usually don't do that.

333
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,834
NEXT, THE SOLO SHOTS!

334
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:50,636
<i>It's the long-awaited solo shots.</i>

335
00:12:52,037 --> 00:12:52,872
GETTING MY SOLO SHOT?

336
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,173
She's really something.

337
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:57,243
-My gosh. Yes.
-She's good.

338
00:12:57,309 --> 00:12:59,411
NEVER-BEFORE-SEEN CUTENESS ON CAMERA

339
00:12:59,478 --> 00:13:01,046
There were international guests too.

340
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:02,648
EXCEEDING THE CUTENESS LIMIT

341
00:13:03,048 --> 00:13:03,883
GUILLERMO DEL TORO

342
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:05,284
Filmmaker Guillermo del Toro.

343
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:07,887
JELLY CHEEKS

344
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:11,524
THE CUTENESS BATTLE YE-EUN STARTED

345
00:13:12,825 --> 00:13:14,360
NEXT UP, A FAMILIAR FACE?

346
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:15,761
-That's Director Kang.
-She was here.

347
00:13:15,828 --> 00:13:17,496
-Director Maggie Kang.
-Director Kang.

348
00:13:17,563 --> 00:13:18,931
SHE BRIGHTENED UP THE BIFF

349
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:22,234
BLUSH

350
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:26,705
The cast of the drama, including me,
made a promise

351
00:13:26,772 --> 00:13:28,440
that if a camera caught us,

352
00:13:28,507 --> 00:13:31,911
we'd make the same pose together.

353
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:33,779
But only I did it. Everyone bailed out.

354
00:13:35,414 --> 00:13:36,916
-After they promised?
-So I just

355
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:39,251
became someone who does weird stuff.

356
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:41,554
Are you usually like that?

357
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:43,923
I was born this way.

358
00:13:43,989 --> 00:13:46,425
-Yes, you were born that way.
-You're like that?

359
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,427
-How cute.
-Are you usually this bubbly?

360
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:50,830
-No, that's not the case.
-It's not?

361
00:13:50,896 --> 00:13:52,464
I'm actually an introvert.

362
00:13:52,531 --> 00:13:55,634
But a place like that has

363
00:13:55,701 --> 00:13:56,769
a solemn atmosphere,

364
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,671
but the weather was so nice,
so I felt like

365
00:13:58,737 --> 00:14:00,472
I was walking through a vast field,

366
00:14:00,539 --> 00:14:02,074
which made me so happy.

367
00:14:02,975 --> 00:14:05,845
That was the perfect vibe
for a festival like that.

368
00:14:05,911 --> 00:14:08,581
-I thought it was great.
-Thank you.

369
00:14:08,647 --> 00:14:11,183
-What if they catch you, Jun-young?
-On camera.

370
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:12,751
Will you do that?

371
00:14:12,818 --> 00:14:14,820
I should, right?

372
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:18,824
This is <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Film Festival.

373
00:14:18,891 --> 00:14:21,927
We're here with so many people.

374
00:14:21,994 --> 00:14:23,128
TA-DA

375
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,396
She's on camera.

376
00:14:24,463 --> 00:14:27,967
As we speak, we're seeing
actor Shin Ye-eun on the screen.

377
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,002
WELCOME, SOLO SHOT

378
00:14:30,069 --> 00:14:31,136
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU

379
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,538
AUTOMATIC BIG SMILES

380
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,073
WHOA… ARGH…

381
00:14:35,407 --> 00:14:36,942
THE CUTENESS MVP'S PRESENCE

382
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:40,346
She's good. She's really different.

383
00:14:40,412 --> 00:14:41,680
This is what I call a festival.

384
00:14:41,747 --> 00:14:43,249
-Cut.
-Next one.

385
00:14:43,315 --> 00:14:44,817
-Whoa.
-Eun-yeong!

386
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,986
Chef Eun-yeong is caught on camera first.

387
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,388
I just… I can't do this.

388
00:14:49,822 --> 00:14:52,258
SURPRISINGLY, SHE CAN'T DO THESE THINGS

389
00:14:52,324 --> 00:14:53,225
She can't do it.

390
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:55,261
NEXT, PLEASE

391
00:14:55,327 --> 00:14:58,130
It's like footage from the news,
the evening news.

392
00:14:58,497 --> 00:14:59,531
THE CRAZY ONE IDENTIFIED

393
00:14:59,598 --> 00:15:00,566
Like a corporate criminal?

394
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:02,301
-"Stop filming me!"
-So it's not just Jun-young?

395
00:15:03,335 --> 00:15:05,104
FINALLY, JUN-YOUNG'S TURN

396
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:08,207
Lee Jun-young!
Actor Lee Jun-young is here too.

397
00:15:08,274 --> 00:15:09,975
STARTS OFF WITH A GREETING

398
00:15:10,676 --> 00:15:12,678
TAKE… THIS!

399
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:15,447
THROWING EVERYTHING HE'S GOT

400
00:15:15,514 --> 00:15:16,882
You're doing good!

401
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:18,384
THE CAMERA IS STILL ON HIM

402
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:22,121
AN INTROVERT DOING HIS BEST TO SURVIVE

403
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:25,391
-He's good when he actually does it.
-Yes.

404
00:15:25,824 --> 00:15:26,959
NEXT UP!

405
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:28,060
A senior actor.

406
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,762
-"A senior actor"?
-"A senior"?

407
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,130
A SENIOR ACTOR IS AMONG US

408
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:33,866
A senior chef,
a seasoned chef is here with us.

409
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:34,900
THAT'S A NO-NO

410
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,969
Give us something cute.

411
00:15:37,036 --> 00:15:38,637
SCREAMING

412
00:15:38,704 --> 00:15:39,672
No, something cute.

413
00:15:40,072 --> 00:15:41,740
HIS CONFIDENCE IS AS GOOD AS A NEW STAR

414
00:15:42,241 --> 00:15:43,309
A LITTLE SOMETHING FOR YOU

415
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,177
WANT TO UNSEE THAT…

416
00:15:45,244 --> 00:15:47,947
There he is. There's Jong-won.

417
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:49,415
What if we didn't get you on camera?

418
00:15:49,481 --> 00:15:50,883
CHECKING FOR THE CAMERA!

419
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,585
-He's our up-and-coming chef.
-He looks cool.

420
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:55,154
SMUG

421
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:58,257
JONG-WON IS TRYING TOO HARD

422
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:00,926
THE INFP FAINTS AFTER A SINGLE UPWARD NOD…

423
00:16:00,993 --> 00:16:02,394
He has it in him.

424
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:03,295
You could do it.

425
00:16:03,362 --> 00:16:06,365
Was that a dance? What is this?

426
00:16:06,432 --> 00:16:08,701
Give us one last shot. The last one.

427
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:10,602
-It's us.
-We're on. Where?

428
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:12,471
What's your plan?

429
00:16:13,539 --> 00:16:14,707
…THE CUTENESS NO ONE ASKED FOR

430
00:16:14,773 --> 00:16:16,976
-That's awful.
-You two are good.

431
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:18,777
You're good at this.

432
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:19,678
A BITE FOR ME

433
00:16:19,745 --> 00:16:20,846
A BITE FOR YOU

434
00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:22,281
That's all.

435
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:23,682
You're good.

436
00:16:23,749 --> 00:16:25,551
YE-EUN SPREAD HER CUTENESS HERE TOO

437
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:27,653
I want to throw something at them.

438
00:16:28,587 --> 00:16:31,724
She is someone who is full of charm,

439
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:35,060
and just like her,
her fridge also seems extraordinary.

440
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:37,429
-Do you live alone?
-Yes.

441
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,064
She mentioned it briefly earlier

442
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:41,000
that she's serious about cooking

443
00:16:41,066 --> 00:16:42,968
and wants to get better at it.

444
00:16:43,035 --> 00:16:45,771
-I'm sure she cooks a lot at home.
-Yes.

445
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:47,973
I'm looking forward to seeing her fridge.

446
00:16:48,207 --> 00:16:49,174
HESITANT

447
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:50,843
I don't have too much food.

448
00:16:50,909 --> 00:16:53,712
Wait, all of a sudden?
I was about to open it now.

449
00:16:53,779 --> 00:16:56,949
I usually have a lot,

450
00:16:57,016 --> 00:17:00,019
-but I've been too busy lately.
-It happens.

451
00:17:00,085 --> 00:17:02,221
The food got spoiled
because I couldn't cook often,

452
00:17:02,287 --> 00:17:04,723
so it's a bit emptier than usual.

453
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:07,393
-We present Ye-eun's fridge!
-Fridge!

454
00:17:07,459 --> 00:17:10,362
FULL OF INTEREST

455
00:17:10,429 --> 00:17:14,133
I see some empty spots here and there.

456
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:17,770
What are these? For <i>gimbap?</i>
Do you make <i>gimbap?</i>

457
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:20,606
I like <i>gimbap</i>.
I like to have many flavors…

458
00:17:20,672 --> 00:17:22,074
I mean, I prefer the kind of food

459
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:25,010
that harmoniously mixes
many different flavors.

460
00:17:25,077 --> 00:17:26,912
Do you make <i>gimbap</i> yourself?

461
00:17:26,979 --> 00:17:30,816
Yes, because I can't get
just one roll of <i>gimbap</i> delivered.

462
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,585
These are the ingredients
I just found here.

463
00:17:33,652 --> 00:17:36,255
Do you add anything else to your gimbap?

464
00:17:36,321 --> 00:17:38,657
-Shishito peppers.
-Shishito peppers.

465
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:42,094
-So these. Right there.
-Right here. Shishito peppers.

466
00:17:42,161 --> 00:17:42,995
You use them uncooked?

467
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:46,498
-Yes.
-Instead of braising them?

468
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:47,866
-No.
-You use them uncooked?

469
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:49,802
-They'll still be spicy.
-They'll be spicy.

470
00:17:49,868 --> 00:17:51,603
They weren't spicy.

471
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,238
-"They weren't spicy"?
-They weren't?

472
00:17:53,305 --> 00:17:56,575
These are often stir-fried
or braised before using.

473
00:17:56,642 --> 00:17:58,877
-Honestly, I don't really remember.
-What?

474
00:17:58,944 --> 00:18:01,580
But you just said you had these recently.

475
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,615
UGH…

476
00:18:03,682 --> 00:18:05,317
-She did.
-Wait a second.

477
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:06,318
-No seasonings?
-Yes!

478
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:09,088
I only added some sesame oil in a pan…
No, wait. The sesame oil…

479
00:18:09,154 --> 00:18:10,789
Why do I sound like I'm lying?

480
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:13,525
HOW CUTE

481
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:16,462
Did you see a frying pan right there?

482
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:20,299
-So you did stir-fry them. In oil.
-I fried them in oil.

483
00:18:20,365 --> 00:18:21,700
That can happen.

484
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,369
You can sometimes blank out
when you suddenly have to answer.

485
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:27,106
The important thing is that she likes food

486
00:18:27,172 --> 00:18:30,576
-that comes with many different flavors.
-Yes.

487
00:18:30,642 --> 00:18:32,478
-Like bibimbap.
-Bibimbap.

488
00:18:32,544 --> 00:18:35,681
You take a bite of many ingredients,
yet it's harmonious.

489
00:18:35,747 --> 00:18:36,648
I see.

490
00:18:36,715 --> 00:18:39,251
-Dumplings.
-She's right.

491
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:41,620
-Pizza.
-Fillings are made with many ingredients.

492
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:43,355
-That's the case with pizza too.
-Pizza.

493
00:18:43,422 --> 00:18:45,090
But one flavor can't stand out.

494
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:46,658
-It can't stand out?
-No.

495
00:18:46,725 --> 00:18:48,760
-They must all work together.
-That's right.

496
00:18:48,827 --> 00:18:50,262
-It needs good chemistry.
-Yes.

497
00:18:50,329 --> 00:18:52,598
You made bibimbap
on that one show I watched.

498
00:18:52,664 --> 00:18:54,166
-Yes, I did.
-Yes.

499
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:57,269
You said you wanted to clarify something
about your cooking skills.

500
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:58,904
-Here's the thing.
-Is that so?

501
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:01,773
I seemed to be bad at cooking
on that show, right?

502
00:19:02,441 --> 00:19:03,375
Agreed.

503
00:19:03,442 --> 00:19:04,610
Agreed.

504
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:05,844
SO CHILL

505
00:19:05,911 --> 00:19:07,813
-You wanted to agree?
-How long ago was it?

506
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:11,383
Since that time, I realized how bad I was.

507
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:14,052
So I tried to cook
a lot more often after that.

508
00:19:14,119 --> 00:19:16,355
When people tell me
that I'm bad at cooking,

509
00:19:16,421 --> 00:19:18,423
it really kills my pride.

510
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,125
-I want to be good at it.
-Many people saw it.

511
00:19:20,192 --> 00:19:23,128
Can you show us
some pictures of the dishes you made?

512
00:19:23,195 --> 00:19:25,898
-I have lots! I've sent lots of them.
-You did?

513
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:27,299
-I see.
-Are those ready?

514
00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:28,600
I'm looking forward to it.

515
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,302
-The dishes Ye-eun made.
-Don't expect too much.

516
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:32,437
-Let's see the pictures.
-Hey.

517
00:19:32,704 --> 00:19:34,373
CLAPPING FOR HERSELF

518
00:19:34,439 --> 00:19:35,941
-Let's see the pictures.
-Hey.

519
00:19:36,808 --> 00:19:38,043
She makes many different dishes.

520
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:39,578
Wait, what about those?

521
00:19:39,645 --> 00:19:40,913
You made the dumplings, right?

522
00:19:40,979 --> 00:19:42,814
-No, I bought those.
-You did?

523
00:19:43,682 --> 00:19:45,584
-He had to point that out first.
-They look too pretty.

524
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:47,819
Tell us about each one.

525
00:19:47,886 --> 00:19:50,622
I wanted to make a pretty rolled omelet,

526
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,692
so I bought the pan
specifically for that purpose.

527
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:55,961
And I tried adding
different ingredients in that.

528
00:19:56,028 --> 00:20:01,033
For the curry, I like to eat
mushrooms as the topping.

529
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:06,004
And that pasta.
I had too many chicken breast sausages

530
00:20:06,071 --> 00:20:08,540
that were about to expire,

531
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:11,410
so it doesn't look so pretty,

532
00:20:11,476 --> 00:20:12,811
but I cleaned out my fridge.

533
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,846
-And… Yes.
-The third one must be <i>bibim-guksu</i>.

534
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:16,848
-With young radish.
-I did a good job with that.

535
00:20:16,915 --> 00:20:18,817
ENDEARING CONFIDENCE

536
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:22,221
You seem to have cut off
the top and the bottom part of the egg.

537
00:20:22,287 --> 00:20:23,522
Was there a reason?

538
00:20:23,589 --> 00:20:25,657
It looks like you split it in half
with your hands.

539
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:28,660
AW…

540
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:30,495
-I used a knife.
-And that happened?

541
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:32,864
-It's usually not that rugged.
-Did she take a bite?

542
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:34,967
Look at that <i>gimbap</i> on the very right.

543
00:20:35,033 --> 00:20:36,835
-With shishito peppers.
-She really made those.

544
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:39,504
I never add cucumbers
to kimchi… I mean, <i>gimbap</i>.

545
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:41,673
-Hey, she knows what's up.
-The scent

546
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,675
stands out too much.

547
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:45,110
That's a shame.

548
00:20:45,177 --> 00:20:47,813
-I see.
-How are the fillings all popping out?

549
00:20:47,879 --> 00:20:49,448
DON'T LOOK TOO CLOSELY

550
00:20:49,514 --> 00:20:51,250
We received a tip.

551
00:20:51,316 --> 00:20:52,884
Ye-eun was invited

552
00:20:52,951 --> 00:20:55,954
to be on <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

553
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:57,990
-What?
-Really?

554
00:20:58,056 --> 00:20:59,658
-It was a tip from her.
-Really?

555
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:01,727
-No.
-Did they contact you?

556
00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:04,563
No, it wasn't that
I got an offer from <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

557
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:06,932
People who tried my food would go,

558
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:09,001
"Hey, why are you so good?"

559
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:09,901
LAUGHING

560
00:21:10,902 --> 00:21:12,604
"You should compete there."

561
00:21:12,671 --> 00:21:14,573
-Right. "You should be on <i>CCW</i>."
-It was like that.

562
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,941
The show was hot at the time.

563
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:18,944
I heard once you're hooked on something,
you only eat that. Is that true?

564
00:21:19,011 --> 00:21:21,747
I only eat that one thing,
so much so that people would ask

565
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:24,483
if I held a share
in that particular place.

566
00:21:24,549 --> 00:21:26,051
Once I find a new favorite restaurant,

567
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:29,187
I'll go there every day of the week
and even bring all my friends.

568
00:21:29,254 --> 00:21:31,056
-I see.
-And I only get that food delivered.

569
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:33,325
What were you hooked on?

570
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:35,127
-Shabu-shabu.
-Shabu-shabu.

571
00:21:35,193 --> 00:21:37,262
-Recently, <i>jjajangmyeon.</i>
<i>-Jjajangmyeon.</i>

572
00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:39,464
-Next, kimchi-<i>jjigae</i>.
-Kimchi stew.

573
00:21:39,531 --> 00:21:41,266
In your opinion,

574
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:43,635
what do you think
is your all-time favorite food?

575
00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:44,803
-Hamburgers.
-Hamburgers?

576
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:46,738
-She likes hamburgers.
-They're good.

577
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,940
-So you like hamburgers.
-Hamburgers are the best.

578
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:50,208
Hamburger is another dish

579
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:54,079
where you can taste
different flavors all at once.

580
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:58,050
I enjoy that flavor
and how it fills up my mouth.

581
00:21:58,116 --> 00:21:59,217
You're right.

582
00:21:59,284 --> 00:22:01,420
This is kind of like my bucket list,

583
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:04,489
so when I go to a new country,
I always try the hamburger there.

584
00:22:04,556 --> 00:22:05,791
-I see.
-However,

585
00:22:05,857 --> 00:22:08,493
not from famous joints, but from places
I come across on the street.

586
00:22:09,561 --> 00:22:11,630
What kind of hamburger do you like?

587
00:22:11,697 --> 00:22:13,332
Something that isn't light.

588
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:14,900
-Not light?
-Not light?

589
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:16,535
Something rich with lots of sauce.

590
00:22:16,601 --> 00:22:18,637
-Something rich?
-Do you need lots of sauce?

591
00:22:18,704 --> 00:22:20,172
A burger that overflows with sauce.

592
00:22:20,238 --> 00:22:21,606
No pickles.

593
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,775
-No pickles?
-Because they stand out?

594
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:24,943
Pickles stand out.

595
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:28,013
And the buns.
Do you know the buns that turn yellow?

596
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:28,914
Sounds like brioche.

597
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:29,948
That's right!

598
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,216
That's right!

599
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:32,551
SURPRISED

600
00:22:32,617 --> 00:22:34,353
-Was there a mosquito?
-Turns yellow?

601
00:22:34,419 --> 00:22:35,921
-It turns yellow?
-"That's right!"

602
00:22:35,987 --> 00:22:38,724
-Yes, the buns turn yellow.
-Yes, the brioche buns.

603
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:39,825
That's how I like it.

604
00:22:39,891 --> 00:22:43,095
You wrote down that
your dream was to own a burger joint.

605
00:22:43,161 --> 00:22:44,262
-Is that true?
-The owner?

606
00:22:44,329 --> 00:22:46,231
That's how much I like it.

607
00:22:46,298 --> 00:22:48,333
I want to keep working harder as an actor

608
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:52,037
to become the owner of a burger joint.
Something like that.

609
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:55,374
-How cute.
-You know,

610
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:57,876
whenever you eat a burger,

611
00:22:57,943 --> 00:23:01,380
-it usually comes with fries too.
-Always.

612
00:23:01,446 --> 00:23:03,315
To our production crew, she said,

613
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:06,752
"I can guess which fries are from
which franchise with my eyes closed."

614
00:23:06,818 --> 00:23:08,019
-That's tough.
-Really?

615
00:23:08,086 --> 00:23:09,654
The future burger joint owner should know.

616
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:12,657
So she offered to do a test.

617
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:14,559
If you succeed,
you're a certified gourmet.

618
00:23:14,626 --> 00:23:19,931
We picked up the fries
from four different fast food restaurants.

619
00:23:19,998 --> 00:23:22,968
Ye-eun, the future burger joint owner,

620
00:23:23,034 --> 00:23:26,538
and Chef Nam-no, the professor of eating,
will do the test.

621
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:29,908
The rest of us and the viewers know
where these are from.

622
00:23:29,975 --> 00:23:30,942
Can you guess these?

623
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:34,045
-If you do, you're on a deity level.
-How can you do this?

624
00:23:34,112 --> 00:23:36,448
Will she rise
as the queen of French fries?

625
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:38,683
-This one.
-The first one. Number one.

626
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,318
You can't give him just one.

627
00:23:40,385 --> 00:23:43,588
-Open up.
-Open up and eat the fry.

628
00:23:43,655 --> 00:23:45,290
-It's good.
-That's number one.

629
00:23:45,357 --> 00:23:47,058
USING ALL OF HER TASTE BUDS

630
00:23:47,125 --> 00:23:49,261
-Give me some more.
-More?

631
00:23:49,327 --> 00:23:51,096
-Some more?
-You can have some more.

632
00:23:51,163 --> 00:23:52,464
Give him lots.

633
00:23:52,531 --> 00:23:53,498
That's too much.

634
00:23:53,565 --> 00:23:55,167
A HANDFUL

635
00:23:55,233 --> 00:23:57,335
Nam-no gets some more.

636
00:23:57,402 --> 00:23:58,670
That's too much.

637
00:23:58,737 --> 00:24:00,138
Isn't this how you eat it?

638
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:01,973
THINKING CAREFULLY

639
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:03,175
You just have to guess it right.

640
00:24:03,241 --> 00:24:04,943
You're like a sommelier for fries.

641
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:06,711
Number two. They'll try everything first.

642
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:08,280
Moving on to number two.

643
00:24:08,346 --> 00:24:10,015
NO. 2 MC*ONALD'S FRENCH FRIES

644
00:24:10,816 --> 00:24:11,683
NOM NOM

645
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:15,454
-It's like he's feeding livestock.
-Livestock?

646
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:17,589
SAVORING CAREFULLY

647
00:24:17,656 --> 00:24:19,357
-Like a barn animal.
-That's the second one.

648
00:24:19,424 --> 00:24:21,092
Is this M brand?

649
00:24:21,159 --> 00:24:22,327
-It's good.
-Is it M brand?

650
00:24:22,594 --> 00:24:24,329
NO WAY!

651
00:24:24,396 --> 00:24:25,897
-Shall we move on?
-The third one.

652
00:24:26,398 --> 00:24:27,966
The third one.

653
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:30,435
NO. 3, BUR*ER KING FRENCH FRIES

654
00:24:31,837 --> 00:24:33,939
That's the third one.

655
00:24:34,005 --> 00:24:35,273
-B brand.
-What?

656
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:37,242
-The third one.
-My gosh.

657
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:41,346
-She says the third one is B brand.
-It only touched her lips.

658
00:24:42,047 --> 00:24:43,248
-But is it right?
-Okay.

659
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:45,083
That guess was almost too quick.

660
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,519
NO. 4, K*C FRENCH FRIES

661
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:49,955
It's like feeding time at the pet zoo.

662
00:24:50,021 --> 00:24:52,991
-He devours it.
-Dad, I want to do that too. Let me do it.

663
00:24:53,058 --> 00:24:54,993
She's serious about fries.

664
00:24:56,795 --> 00:24:58,663
She must know.

665
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:00,866
Is number four K brand?

666
00:25:00,932 --> 00:25:03,101
-Number four, K brand.
-Number four.

667
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:05,136
Was that a question or your final answer?

668
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:07,138
An answer.

669
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:09,407
I haven't had K brand
for the last few years,

670
00:25:09,474 --> 00:25:11,576
-so I'm not sure.
-Number four, K brand.

671
00:25:11,643 --> 00:25:14,746
Now, it's time to give us the answer.

672
00:25:14,813 --> 00:25:18,316
Number one.
Which brand are the first fries from?

673
00:25:18,383 --> 00:25:19,284
Fries number one.

674
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:20,252
It has that fat flavor.

675
00:25:20,318 --> 00:25:22,254
L brand. M brand.

676
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:24,122
CORRECT, CORRECT

677
00:25:24,189 --> 00:25:25,490
B brand. K brand.

678
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:27,726
ALL CORRECT

679
00:25:27,959 --> 00:25:29,227
AMAZED

680
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:31,029
-Is that it?
-Are you sure?

681
00:25:31,096 --> 00:25:32,597
That's her final answer.

682
00:25:32,664 --> 00:25:33,965
-Nam-no.
-Nam-no.

683
00:25:34,032 --> 00:25:35,767
M brand. L brand.

684
00:25:36,501 --> 00:25:37,469
B brand.

685
00:25:38,803 --> 00:25:40,505
-K brand.
-I see.

686
00:25:40,572 --> 00:25:44,776
-Different answers for number one and two.
-Only two are different.

687
00:25:44,843 --> 00:25:46,611
Take your eye masks off

688
00:25:46,678 --> 00:25:48,213
and check the answer.

689
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,514
One, two, three.

690
00:25:49,581 --> 00:25:51,550
-What's the answer?
-Where are they?

691
00:25:51,616 --> 00:25:53,318
Number one, L brand. Two, M brand.

692
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:55,587
Three, B brand. Four, K brand.

693
00:25:55,654 --> 00:25:57,088
-Ye-eun was correct!
-How did she do it?

694
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:59,391
-How did she do this?
-Yes, how?

695
00:25:59,457 --> 00:26:00,959
-Ye-eun wins!
-Thank you.

696
00:26:01,026 --> 00:26:02,160
That's amazing.

697
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:04,496
FORGETTING THE PAIN OF DEFEAT WITH FRIES…

698
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:06,998
-L, M, B, and K brands.
-How did she guess only by the fries?

699
00:26:07,065 --> 00:26:10,402
We hereby certify Ye-eun
as a burger enthusiast.

700
00:26:10,468 --> 00:26:14,105
CERTIFIED HAMBURGER ENTHUSIAST

701
00:26:14,339 --> 00:26:15,807
AMAZED

702
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:18,209
You definitely qualify
to own a burger joint.

703
00:26:18,276 --> 00:26:19,978
Thank you.

704
00:26:20,045 --> 00:26:21,780
There are veggies down here.

705
00:26:21,846 --> 00:26:25,617
Romaine, perilla leaves, carrots,
and many more.

706
00:26:25,684 --> 00:26:27,652
On this side is the freezer.

707
00:26:27,719 --> 00:26:29,087
-<i>Cheonggukjang</i>.
-<i>Cheonggukjang</i>?

708
00:26:29,154 --> 00:26:30,388
Do you like <i>cheonggukjang</i>?

709
00:26:30,455 --> 00:26:31,823
Yes, I'm good at making it.

710
00:26:31,890 --> 00:26:33,458
You do make lots of Korean food at home.

711
00:26:33,525 --> 00:26:35,060
-I do.
-Yes, you make <i>gimbap</i>

712
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:37,162
and <i>cheonggukjang</i> at home too.

713
00:26:37,228 --> 00:26:40,231
Pork. And some beef.

714
00:26:40,298 --> 00:26:42,000
I see some <i>mandu</i>, dumplings in here.

715
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:44,402
-<i>Mandu</i>.
-I love dumplings.

716
00:26:44,469 --> 00:26:46,605
Next, shelf-stable ingredients.

717
00:26:46,671 --> 00:26:48,239
I see some tea bags.

718
00:26:48,306 --> 00:26:51,242
-Yes, I enjoy tea. I can't drink coffee.
-Tea.

719
00:26:51,309 --> 00:26:53,278
So I usually take those with me.

720
00:26:53,345 --> 00:26:56,314
-And some pasta.
-Pasta.

721
00:26:56,381 --> 00:26:58,016
You must make pasta often too.

722
00:26:58,083 --> 00:26:59,851
I like pasta. And other noodle dishes too.

723
00:26:59,918 --> 00:27:01,486
-We saw it in the photo.
-Yes.

724
00:27:01,553 --> 00:27:02,687
Do you also like <i>ramyeon</i>?

725
00:27:02,754 --> 00:27:03,822
I love <i>ramyeon</i>.

726
00:27:03,888 --> 00:27:06,691
I tend to leave it and let it get soggy.

727
00:27:06,758 --> 00:27:09,260
-Instead of firm noodles?
-Not the firm ones.

728
00:27:09,327 --> 00:27:10,228
-Soggy noodles?
-Yes.

729
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,529
-Soggy noodles?
-Overcooked.

730
00:27:12,097 --> 00:27:13,698
I see.

731
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:17,335
I'm not so sure whether
she's actually good at cooking or not.

732
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:20,338
But she does have clear preferences

733
00:27:20,405 --> 00:27:23,608
-when it comes to food.
-She does. Is she good at cooking or not?

734
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:26,645
I also want to find out
what her orders are today.

735
00:27:26,711 --> 00:27:29,614
Here are the dishes
that Ye-eun wants to eat.

736
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:31,049
Here are her orders.

737
00:27:31,116 --> 00:27:32,951
What does Ye-eun want to eat?

738
00:27:33,518 --> 00:27:35,887
I Craved Burgers to Death.

739
00:27:35,954 --> 00:27:38,023
<i>-I missed you to death.</i>
-From <i>The Glory</i>.

740
00:27:38,089 --> 00:27:39,858
I Craved Burgers to Death.

741
00:27:39,924 --> 00:27:42,994
I want to eat a burger
that's only made for me,

742
00:27:43,061 --> 00:27:46,731
-something only I can try.
-The only one.

743
00:27:46,798 --> 00:27:48,466
Burgers just for Ye-eun.

744
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:50,902
And the second order.
What's her second order?

745
00:27:50,969 --> 00:27:53,471
A New Dish That'll Surpass Burgers.

746
00:27:53,538 --> 00:27:55,740
-What's this?
-That's even harder.

747
00:27:55,807 --> 00:27:58,610
Once I'm hooked on a particular dish,
I only eat that.

748
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:00,879
Other than burgers,

749
00:28:00,945 --> 00:28:03,748
make me something
that I'll crave every single day.

750
00:28:03,815 --> 00:28:05,450
Something that's addictive.

751
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:07,252
But nothing that smells too strong,

752
00:28:07,318 --> 00:28:08,420
such as <i>mala</i> or truffles.

753
00:28:08,486 --> 00:28:11,256
I like mushrooms,
but nothing too strong like truffles.

754
00:28:11,322 --> 00:28:14,159
They can only use the ingredients
from your fridge, you see?

755
00:28:14,225 --> 00:28:15,794
You don't have truffles.

756
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:16,895
Oh!

757
00:28:16,961 --> 00:28:17,862
You're right.

758
00:28:17,929 --> 00:28:20,532
This isn't exactly a restaurant.

759
00:28:20,598 --> 00:28:24,602
Among the eight chefs,
who's going to jump in?

760
00:28:24,669 --> 00:28:26,771
-We're joining now? I'm in.
-Let's see.

761
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:28,239
YOON NAM-NO?

762
00:28:28,306 --> 00:28:29,641
-Join where?
-Nam-no?

763
00:28:29,708 --> 00:28:31,109
-I want to go.
-Go where?

764
00:28:31,776 --> 00:28:32,811
Go home?

765
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:35,146
GOING HOME AFTER EATING FRIES?

766
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,382
I'm going for I Craved Burgers to Death.

767
00:28:37,449 --> 00:28:40,285
-I Craved Burgers to Death.
-It suits him.

768
00:28:40,351 --> 00:28:42,220
Are you just saying
you're craving burgers?

769
00:28:42,287 --> 00:28:45,056
-What do you mean?
-Understand the assignment first, okay?

770
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:47,459
You're making burgers.

771
00:28:47,525 --> 00:28:49,494
I can make two and eat one.

772
00:28:49,861 --> 00:28:51,129
WHAT A… GENIUS…

773
00:28:51,196 --> 00:28:52,497
Can you make good burgers?

774
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:54,365
After all, I even look like one.

775
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:55,366
That's true.

776
00:28:55,433 --> 00:28:57,068
-"Look like one"?
-You look like a burger?

777
00:28:57,135 --> 00:28:58,737
He has two patties
on the back of his neck.

778
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:00,605
BIG NECK

779
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:03,575
A BORN BURGER COOK

780
00:29:03,641 --> 00:29:05,143
A burger just for Ye-eun.

781
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:06,611
Nam-no joins the round.

782
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:08,580
-All right.
-Who wants to go next?

783
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:09,948
Kwon Sung-jun.

784
00:29:10,014 --> 00:29:11,249
What? Come at me.

785
00:29:11,316 --> 00:29:14,419
I'm someone who once
revolutionized hamburgers in Korea, so…

786
00:29:14,486 --> 00:29:16,020
When? When did you do that?

787
00:29:16,287 --> 00:29:17,822
NEWS TO ME

788
00:29:17,889 --> 00:29:19,858
When did you revolutionize hamburgers?

789
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:22,127
I made
the highest-selling hamburger in Korea.

790
00:29:22,193 --> 00:29:23,828
-I had it often.
-Is that so?

791
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:26,498
Six million burgers were sold
just last year.

792
00:29:26,564 --> 00:29:27,799
-Really?
-Yes.

793
00:29:27,866 --> 00:29:29,234
Yet you're not joining the burger round?

794
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:31,770
I've already made a new wave,
so I'll make something different.

795
00:29:31,836 --> 00:29:34,005
So you'll make something
that surpasses burgers?

796
00:29:34,072 --> 00:29:35,707
-She said she'd eat it every day.
-Yes.

797
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:37,275
So when she eats, you know…

798
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:40,245
She might think of me.

799
00:29:40,311 --> 00:29:41,446
Think of you?

800
00:29:43,014 --> 00:29:44,249
UGH!

801
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:46,084
-How scary.
-So I'll go with the second one.

802
00:29:46,151 --> 00:29:47,952
I think he's going to make <i>sujebi</i> for her.

803
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:50,855
-By pulling this dough.
-A bowl of sujebi.

804
00:29:51,189 --> 00:29:52,624
SWOOSH

805
00:29:52,690 --> 00:29:55,093
-Sung-jun will make a new dish.
-<i>Sujebi</i>.

806
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:57,595
-These two split up.
-Poong?

807
00:29:57,662 --> 00:29:59,364
-Huh?
-Poong.

808
00:29:59,430 --> 00:30:00,498
Is he going for Nam-no?

809
00:30:00,565 --> 00:30:01,733
Wait, why? Again?

810
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,967
ANXIOUS

811
00:30:03,034 --> 00:30:04,035
I am

812
00:30:04,903 --> 00:30:06,971
Kim Poong, someone who always makes

813
00:30:07,038 --> 00:30:09,140
something new
that surpasses people's expectations.

814
00:30:09,407 --> 00:30:11,242
THAT WAS SO CLOSE…

815
00:30:11,309 --> 00:30:12,877
I'll make something new

816
00:30:12,944 --> 00:30:15,814
that surpasses burgers
and will make her eat it every day

817
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:17,916
for at least one year.

818
00:30:17,982 --> 00:30:19,217
RISING EXPECTATIONS

819
00:30:19,284 --> 00:30:21,986
-But everything he makes is new.
-Yes.

820
00:30:22,253 --> 00:30:24,789
MOST OF HIS DISHES ARE ONE OF A KIND

821
00:30:24,856 --> 00:30:26,791
-One spot remains for burgers.
-Hamburgers.

822
00:30:26,858 --> 00:30:29,127
-I'll make it.
-Really?

823
00:30:29,194 --> 00:30:31,329
I also love burgers so much.

824
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:34,399
I always visit a burger joint
whenever I'm abroad,

825
00:30:34,465 --> 00:30:37,468
so I have a map
of delicious places all around the world.

826
00:30:37,535 --> 00:30:38,803
-Really?
-Okay.

827
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:40,872
She said she wanted to eat
a new kind of burger.

828
00:30:40,939 --> 00:30:42,540
Save your spiel for the cook-off.

829
00:30:42,607 --> 00:30:43,875
The ordinary…

830
00:30:44,609 --> 00:30:46,978
During the cook-off, please.
I just got the message.

831
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:49,214
-We got a call.
-You were talking for too long.

832
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,982
You can share the rest
during the cook-off.

833
00:30:51,049 --> 00:30:52,951
-Keep it short.
-I'm just relaying the message.

834
00:30:53,017 --> 00:30:55,019
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

835
00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:56,688
The thing is,

836
00:30:56,754 --> 00:30:59,324
-what she wants is a new kind of burger.
-Yes.

837
00:30:59,390 --> 00:31:03,228
The chef who turns
the ordinary into something new.

838
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:04,295
Who do you think that is?

839
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:06,030
-Choi Hyun-suk.
-Precisely.

840
00:31:06,097 --> 00:31:09,067
Moving on. The matches have been made.

841
00:31:09,133 --> 00:31:11,436
First, the burger cook-off.

842
00:31:11,502 --> 00:31:14,405
Let's begin the round
between Nam-no and Hyun-suk!

843
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:22,413
<i>This is the first round of cook-off</i>
<i>with ingredients from Ye-eun's fridge.</i>

844
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:25,450
The chef whose apron
is a size too small, Chef Yoon Nam-no,

845
00:31:26,184 --> 00:31:27,652
versus the chef

846
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:31,122
who is a bit older than how he feels,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

847
00:31:31,189 --> 00:31:32,790
Nam-no seems

848
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:35,960
-more relaxed with the new apron.
-He looks more at ease.

849
00:31:36,027 --> 00:31:38,296
I ripped the old one apart.

850
00:31:38,363 --> 00:31:39,397
Good call.

851
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:42,667
-Someone said something aggressive.
-What was it?

852
00:31:42,734 --> 00:31:45,136
-It's something Nam-no said.
-What did he say?

853
00:31:45,203 --> 00:31:46,638
Good grief.

854
00:31:46,704 --> 00:31:49,474
"Does a grandpa even know
what good burgers taste like?"

855
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:51,442
Oh, my god.

856
00:31:51,509 --> 00:31:53,244
That was way too harsh.

857
00:31:53,311 --> 00:31:56,581
Chef Nam-no supposedly said
if I knew anything about burgers?

858
00:31:56,648 --> 00:31:59,017
Do you know when hamburgers
were first introduced in Korea?

859
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:00,285
DO YOU EVEN KNOW?

860
00:32:00,351 --> 00:32:01,719
We don't know that.

861
00:32:01,786 --> 00:32:05,023
-We don't. Do you know?
-It's another history special.

862
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:07,058
-The history of burgers.
-The 1988 Olympics.

863
00:32:07,125 --> 00:32:10,261
Does anyone here know Big Boy Burger,
which was sold out of a handcart?

864
00:32:10,328 --> 00:32:13,298
-We don't.
-We don't know.

865
00:32:13,364 --> 00:32:15,400
-A handcart?
-Big Boy Burger?

866
00:32:15,466 --> 00:32:18,202
It began with Big Boy Burger,
hamburgers with cabbage in them.

867
00:32:18,269 --> 00:32:20,705
I know all about the history
of hamburgers in Korea,

868
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:23,541
as well as delicious joints
all around the world.

869
00:32:23,608 --> 00:32:25,043
The sheer amount

870
00:32:25,109 --> 00:32:27,979
of breadcrumbs I have dropped
while eating burgers

871
00:32:28,046 --> 00:32:29,614
is more than enough to make

872
00:32:29,681 --> 00:32:32,216
about 100 graves that can fit Nam-no.

873
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:33,952
"I'll use my crumbs to make your grave."

874
00:32:34,018 --> 00:32:36,354
-He'll bury him.
-You'll make his grave?

875
00:32:36,421 --> 00:32:38,656
Once again,
I think I picked the wrong fight.

876
00:32:39,090 --> 00:32:40,091
PICKED A FIGHT WITH THE WRONG GRANDPA

877
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:42,660
-He thought, "What does a grandpa know?"
-Right?

878
00:32:42,727 --> 00:32:45,463
-He's about to learn a harsh lesson.
-He is.

879
00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:49,133
Nam-no often misunderstands
the intention of the order, doesn't he?

880
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,536
And he's also not up to date
on the latest news.

881
00:32:51,602 --> 00:32:53,404
-There's news?
-Actually,

882
00:32:53,471 --> 00:32:55,807
Hyun-suk recently went to New York

883
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:57,942
and held a huge hamburger event.

884
00:32:58,009 --> 00:32:59,744
-He did.
-In New York?

885
00:32:59,811 --> 00:33:02,013
Yes, it ended very successfully,

886
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:03,982
and he's known
as the Hamburger Grandpa in New York.

887
00:33:04,048 --> 00:33:06,651
-The word got around.
-Burger Choi.

888
00:33:06,718 --> 00:33:08,953
We sometimes call grandpa
a granddad, right?

889
00:33:09,020 --> 00:33:11,723
So people shortened his nickname
and calls him Hamgranddad.

890
00:33:11,789 --> 00:33:15,159
-Or Hamgramps with gramps.
-The granddad.

891
00:33:15,226 --> 00:33:17,195
Why didn't you tell us about it?

892
00:33:17,261 --> 00:33:18,963
-It was a success.
-That's great news.

893
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:21,499
It's not even a big deal.

894
00:33:21,866 --> 00:33:24,235
THERE'S NO NEED FOR ME TO TELL YOU

895
00:33:24,302 --> 00:33:25,870
I did a pop-up store there,

896
00:33:25,937 --> 00:33:28,106
limited to 500 people,

897
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:30,975
-but 800 showed up. Not a big deal.
-Really?

898
00:33:31,042 --> 00:33:32,577
Eight hundred people showed up?

899
00:33:32,643 --> 00:33:35,313
-We have a video from the scene.
-Really?

900
00:33:35,380 --> 00:33:37,315
We didn't have to find one.
He sent it to us.

901
00:33:37,382 --> 00:33:40,551
He sent it to show us?

902
00:33:40,618 --> 00:33:43,454
Let's see the video from the pop-up store
and check how popular it was.

903
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:45,690
This is New York.

904
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:47,392
-Hey.
-This is it.

905
00:33:47,458 --> 00:33:48,359
PROVIDED BY CHOI HYUN-SUK

906
00:33:48,426 --> 00:33:49,494
Look at the line.

907
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:51,029
-No way.
-Non-Koreans are there too.

908
00:33:51,095 --> 00:33:52,497
It's like the line for the World Cup.

909
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:55,600
How far does the line stretch?

910
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:59,570
THE LINE DOUBLES BACK AND KEEPS GOING!

911
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,239
Is that Nam-no?

912
00:34:01,739 --> 00:34:04,042
DOPPELGÄNGER SILHOUETTE

913
00:34:04,308 --> 00:34:05,176
AMAZED

914
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:07,178
It's not even a big deal.

915
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:10,915
It would've been great
if the video started with you, though.

916
00:34:10,982 --> 00:34:12,350
Right? We can't tell what event was.

917
00:34:12,417 --> 00:34:13,985
It was a random video of a line.

918
00:34:14,285 --> 00:34:16,054
SUSPECTING THE AUTHENTICITY

919
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:18,089
It could've been a Nike store.

920
00:34:18,156 --> 00:34:19,257
-Yes.
-Or an Apple store.

921
00:34:19,323 --> 00:34:21,025
-He's right.
-You can't tell.

922
00:34:21,092 --> 00:34:22,660
Ye-eun dreams of owning a burger joint,

923
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:25,596
so please make burgers
that she will absolutely love.

924
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:28,533
CHEF NAM-NO'S INGREDIENTS:
SHRIMP MEAT, SQUID, ENOKI, SHISHITO PEPPER

925
00:34:28,599 --> 00:34:30,601
PERILLA LEAF, ROMAINE, SEAWEED,
OYSTER SAUCE, SRIRACHA, MAYONNAISE

926
00:34:30,668 --> 00:34:33,104
The burger I'm going to make is

927
00:34:33,771 --> 00:34:35,173
Burger War King.

928
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:36,941
-Burger War King?
-Burger War King?

929
00:34:37,008 --> 00:34:38,342
Burger War King.

930
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:40,545
-Burger War King.
-Burger War King.

931
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:43,081
Burger War. Burger War King.

932
00:34:43,147 --> 00:34:44,449
It must be huge.

933
00:34:44,515 --> 00:34:45,450
Is it a hamburger?

934
00:34:45,516 --> 00:34:47,552
Well, it is a burger.

935
00:34:47,618 --> 00:34:49,587
But the buns

936
00:34:49,654 --> 00:34:51,823
-aren't made of bread.
-What? Then?

937
00:34:51,889 --> 00:34:53,491
I'm using rice.

938
00:34:53,558 --> 00:34:54,425
Rice burger?

939
00:34:54,492 --> 00:34:56,260
-Rice burger?
-Rice burger?

940
00:34:56,327 --> 00:34:59,430
I won't be using regular rice, though.

941
00:34:59,497 --> 00:35:01,065
I'm using sushi vinegar.

942
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:03,000
-With sushi rice?
-That's just sushi.

943
00:35:03,067 --> 00:35:05,436
-I'll grill the sushi rice, and…
-He's making sushi?

944
00:35:05,503 --> 00:35:06,604
Grill the sushi rice?

945
00:35:06,671 --> 00:35:08,306
-Wow.
-I'll grill the sushi rice

946
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:11,676
and add a patty
made with squid and shrimp inside.

947
00:35:11,742 --> 00:35:13,578
-That's not a burger.
-Then I'll wrap it…

948
00:35:13,644 --> 00:35:15,513
-That's odd.
-That's not a burger.

949
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:18,716
I'm sorry, but are you talking about
stacking two rice balls together?

950
00:35:18,783 --> 00:35:19,984
-That's it.
-It's just a stack.

951
00:35:20,051 --> 00:35:22,653
-It's like triangular <i>gimbap</i>.
-Triangular <i>gimbap</i>.

952
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:25,756
No, what you're talking about
is triangular <i>gimbap</i>.

953
00:35:25,823 --> 00:35:28,025
-Mine is square.
-Square <i>gimbap</i>.

954
00:35:28,092 --> 00:35:30,728
THE TOPIC IS HAMBURGERS…

955
00:35:30,795 --> 00:35:32,530
That's just a square <i>gimbap</i>.

956
00:35:32,597 --> 00:35:33,965
-Anyway…
-Again…

957
00:35:34,031 --> 00:35:35,533
That's the next round, not this one.

958
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,501
Wait, what now?

959
00:35:36,734 --> 00:35:38,936
A NEW DISH THAT'LL SURPASS BURGERS

960
00:35:39,003 --> 00:35:42,473
-Read it twice before you join a round.
-Did he get the orders confused?

961
00:35:42,540 --> 00:35:44,509
But it will be presented
in a burger form, right?

962
00:35:44,575 --> 00:35:45,610
-It's a burger.
-Right?

963
00:35:45,676 --> 00:35:47,145
It'll look like a burger, right?

964
00:35:47,211 --> 00:35:50,414
-A burger.
-Yes, but you were describing sushi.

965
00:35:50,481 --> 00:35:52,116
Burger made with sushi.

966
00:35:52,450 --> 00:35:54,685
HOW WILL THAT TURN OUT?

967
00:35:54,752 --> 00:35:57,722
-It sounds like war just to hear it.
-Very much so.

968
00:35:57,788 --> 00:35:59,957
-It's like war.
-It's Burger War King.

969
00:36:00,024 --> 00:36:01,893
Let's wait and see what he makes.

970
00:36:02,827 --> 00:36:04,829
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
SIRLOIN, RIB MEAT, ENOKI, SHISHITO PEPPER

971
00:36:04,896 --> 00:36:06,864
BREAD, HAMBURGER BUN, CHEDDAR,
STRAWBERRY JAM, EGG SOY SAUCE, AND MORE

972
00:36:06,931 --> 00:36:08,799
Here's the name of my burger.

973
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:11,669
Five Five Guys.

974
00:36:13,204 --> 00:36:15,973
-Five Five Guys.
-You're using fifty-five again?

975
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:18,442
-Come on.
-Not Senior No. 55?

976
00:36:18,509 --> 00:36:21,512
Senior No. 55.

977
00:36:21,879 --> 00:36:24,515
HIS FIRST MASTERPIECE
TURNED OUT SUCCESSFULLY

978
00:36:27,318 --> 00:36:29,754
-Five Five Guys?
-The age fifty-five burger.

979
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:31,689
A 55-YEAR-OLD GUY'S

980
00:36:31,756 --> 00:36:32,957
-Age 55?
-Really?

981
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:34,792
Grandpa burger.

982
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:36,928
-Oh, no.
-It's a grandpa burger.

983
00:36:36,994 --> 00:36:38,763
He endorsed the grandpa brand.

984
00:36:38,829 --> 00:36:40,731
He modeled for the grandpa brand.

985
00:36:41,065 --> 00:36:43,668
A PERFECT MODEL

986
00:36:43,734 --> 00:36:45,670
So what's your burger like?

987
00:36:45,736 --> 00:36:47,872
The first characteristic is this.

988
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:51,175
I'll mix the muscle
and the fat of the meat evenly

989
00:36:51,242 --> 00:36:53,344
and do meat blending.

990
00:36:54,745 --> 00:36:57,815
-He's making ground beef.
-The ground beef mix.

991
00:36:57,882 --> 00:37:00,451
You're using lots of English
after your trip to New York.

992
00:37:00,518 --> 00:37:03,387
Next, I want to bring out
the umami of enoki mushrooms,

993
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:05,122
so it'll be deep-fried…

994
00:37:05,189 --> 00:37:06,724
DEEP-FRIED = FRITTER

995
00:37:06,791 --> 00:37:08,960
Don't you think
you're deep-frying enoki too often?

996
00:37:09,026 --> 00:37:11,696
Poong has been making chili oil
for the last ten years.

997
00:37:11,762 --> 00:37:13,497
I only deep-fried enoki three times,

998
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:15,233
and you're criticizing me for that?

999
00:37:15,299 --> 00:37:17,335
The guests are always new,
so why does it matter?

1000
00:37:17,401 --> 00:37:18,769
If you will criticize anyone,

1001
00:37:18,836 --> 00:37:22,540
-criticize Poong first. Slap him first!
-Why me?

1002
00:37:22,607 --> 00:37:24,508
Why are you dragging me into this?

1003
00:37:24,575 --> 00:37:27,712
-He's not even a chef.
-"No one criticizes Poong, leave me be."

1004
00:37:27,778 --> 00:37:30,448
-Okay. Fine. As long as it's good.
-Exactly.

1005
00:37:30,514 --> 00:37:33,117
You also love French fries,

1006
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:36,587
but I'll make a new kind of fritter
on the side

1007
00:37:36,654 --> 00:37:38,856
-and balance out my dish.
-A new kind of fritter.

1008
00:37:38,923 --> 00:37:40,558
-I'm curious.
-What's he making?

1009
00:37:40,625 --> 00:37:42,326
And now,

1010
00:37:42,393 --> 00:37:43,861
-Wow.
-let us begin

1011
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:46,897
-This is so cool.
-the round for Shin Ye-eun,

1012
00:37:46,964 --> 00:37:48,165
I Craved Burgers to Death.

1013
00:37:48,232 --> 00:37:50,601
-What's he doing?
-He claims that he owes 80% of his shape

1014
00:37:50,668 --> 00:37:52,370
to hamburgers.

1015
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:54,805
The man who looks like a burger,
Chef Yoon Nam-no.

1016
00:37:55,606 --> 00:37:59,577
The hamburger gramps
who took over New York with his burgers,

1017
00:37:59,644 --> 00:38:01,946
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

1018
00:38:02,013 --> 00:38:05,716
Which one of them will make
the best burger of Ye-eun's life?

1019
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:06,784
And now…

1020
00:38:06,851 --> 00:38:09,954
I Craved Burgers to Death.

1021
00:38:10,021 --> 00:38:12,323
…let the cook-off begin!

1022
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:14,225
…begin!

1023
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:15,259
HAMBURGER♡

1024
00:38:15,326 --> 00:38:17,628
Please make delicious burgers for Ye-eun.

1025
00:38:17,695 --> 00:38:19,630
First, he starts out with rice.

1026
00:38:19,697 --> 00:38:22,300
-Rice first.
-He microwaves instant rice first.

1027
00:38:22,366 --> 00:38:24,235
He has to make sushi rice.

1028
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:26,504
-And he said he'd grill it.
-He did.

1029
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:28,806
-He has to make rice.
-He's making sushi vinegar.

1030
00:38:28,873 --> 00:38:30,775
-Yes, he's using vinegar.
-That's so cool.

1031
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:31,676
SLICE

1032
00:38:31,742 --> 00:38:33,644
Is that beef, Chef Hyun-suk?

1033
00:38:33,711 --> 00:38:35,179
Yes, I'm taking many different cuts

1034
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:36,714
and blending them…

1035
00:38:38,649 --> 00:38:40,951
Why do you have
the <i>ramyeon </i>soup base packet there?

1036
00:38:41,018 --> 00:38:42,420
I'm using it.

1037
00:38:42,486 --> 00:38:44,622
-It must be for the enoki.
-Enoki and <i>ramyeon</i> soup base.

1038
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:46,290
-Poong made that.
-Exactly.

1039
00:38:46,857 --> 00:38:48,859
-No, he's doing that again?
-You're doing that?

1040
00:38:48,926 --> 00:38:50,194
No way he's doing that.

1041
00:38:50,261 --> 00:38:52,029
-He…
-He didn't originate it. It was mine.

1042
00:38:52,096 --> 00:38:52,997
You did?

1043
00:38:53,364 --> 00:38:54,498
YEAH, SURE

1044
00:38:54,565 --> 00:38:55,966
Be careful, Chef Ho-young.

1045
00:38:58,903 --> 00:39:00,671
I'm way too close to him.

1046
00:39:00,971 --> 00:39:04,608
HAMBURGER GRAMPS
GOES FOR THE CLASSIC BEEF PATTY

1047
00:39:05,076 --> 00:39:07,411
-The shrimp and squid patty.
-Squid patty.

1048
00:39:07,478 --> 00:39:08,913
Squid.

1049
00:39:09,747 --> 00:39:12,650
Nam-no grinds squid.

1050
00:39:12,717 --> 00:39:15,119
-Is he making a patty?
-That's right.

1051
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:17,288
Actually, it's not a burger
if you do not use beef.

1052
00:39:17,355 --> 00:39:20,224
-The patty must be beef?
-But what about fish burgers?

1053
00:39:20,291 --> 00:39:22,460
That's a fish sandwich.
Burgers are supposed to be made with beef.

1054
00:39:22,526 --> 00:39:24,895
-It has to be beef.
-Is that so?

1055
00:39:24,962 --> 00:39:27,198
Ye-eun, do you like your burgers

1056
00:39:27,264 --> 00:39:29,266
with a beef patty or a seafood patty?

1057
00:39:29,333 --> 00:39:31,702
It depends on
what I'm craving on that day.

1058
00:39:32,036 --> 00:39:33,237
SHE DODGED IT SMOOTHLY

1059
00:39:33,304 --> 00:39:34,372
Which do you like better?

1060
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:36,474
Are you feeling like
meat or seafood today?

1061
00:39:36,707 --> 00:39:38,209
WHAT IF YOU HAD TO CHOOSE JUST ONE?

1062
00:39:38,275 --> 00:39:40,111
-I'm starving, so both.
-Both?

1063
00:39:40,177 --> 00:39:43,147
-I've skipped my meals today for this.
-Seafood also has a chance.

1064
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:45,149
WHY IS HE CHOPPING SQUID WITH A KNIFE?

1065
00:39:45,583 --> 00:39:48,219
-Chef Nam-no makes a seafood patty.
-That's right.

1066
00:39:48,919 --> 00:39:51,322
OYSTER SAUCE, SUGAR, SALT

1067
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:53,090
That looks so good.

1068
00:39:53,157 --> 00:39:54,892
There's not enough time.

1069
00:39:55,359 --> 00:39:56,727
PREPPING MEAT FOR 1 AND A HALF MINUTES

1070
00:39:56,794 --> 00:39:58,462
Chef Hyun-suk is working on beef patties.

1071
00:39:58,529 --> 00:40:00,998
-Is that the patty?
-Yes.

1072
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:02,900
There's a difference between patties.

1073
00:40:02,967 --> 00:40:06,370
I'm mixing finely and roughly ground beef
to layer the textures.

1074
00:40:06,437 --> 00:40:08,305
-I see.
-That's him.

1075
00:40:08,372 --> 00:40:10,608
He's going to add a fun texture.

1076
00:40:10,875 --> 00:40:12,877
HIS HANDS ARE FASTER THAN HIS EYES!

1077
00:40:12,943 --> 00:40:14,278
SMACK

1078
00:40:14,345 --> 00:40:16,914
He must've done that in New York

1079
00:40:16,981 --> 00:40:18,616
for the New Yorkers.

1080
00:40:18,682 --> 00:40:19,850
Wow.

1081
00:40:19,917 --> 00:40:21,452
He made a ball of patty.

1082
00:40:22,453 --> 00:40:24,321
It's been two minutes already.

1083
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:25,990
INSTANT RICE WARMED UP

1084
00:40:26,056 --> 00:40:28,125
He's already pulling out the instant rice.

1085
00:40:28,192 --> 00:40:30,060
TAKING AN UNCONVENTIONAL APPROACH
WITH RICE

1086
00:40:30,127 --> 00:40:32,963
-Chef Nam-no makes sushi rice.
-Right.

1087
00:40:33,030 --> 00:40:34,999
He's going to use rice as the buns.

1088
00:40:35,065 --> 00:40:36,534
-Yes.
-And he'll have to grill it.

1089
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,569
-He's using cookie cutters.
-Cookie cutters.

1090
00:40:38,636 --> 00:40:41,138
Just like that.
But will the rice stick together?

1091
00:40:41,205 --> 00:40:42,773
After all, he used vinegar.

1092
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:43,941
It won't stick too easily.

1093
00:40:44,008 --> 00:40:45,342
It's flying all over the place.

1094
00:40:45,409 --> 00:40:47,378
Do people eat grilled sushi rice?

1095
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,113
It's a thing
in American sushi restaurants.

1096
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,515
It's topped with tartare and whatnot.

1097
00:40:51,582 --> 00:40:53,784
What's Nam-no doing?

1098
00:40:53,851 --> 00:40:55,953
-He's pressing on it.
-Is he laying the foundation?

1099
00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:58,489
-He's doing it to shape the rice.
-Like scorched rice?

1100
00:40:58,556 --> 00:41:00,958
It will be scorched a little.

1101
00:41:01,192 --> 00:41:02,593
CHOI HYUN-SUK USES ENOKI MUSHROOM!

1102
00:41:03,027 --> 00:41:04,028
OH, MY!

1103
00:41:04,094 --> 00:41:06,297
-Oh, no!
-No!

1104
00:41:06,363 --> 00:41:07,665
Look at him!

1105
00:41:07,731 --> 00:41:09,200
-He's not as strong anymore.
-Right?

1106
00:41:09,266 --> 00:41:10,634
TRIGGERED…

1107
00:41:10,701 --> 00:41:12,503
He used up all his energy
kneading the meat.

1108
00:41:12,570 --> 00:41:15,840
-He put all his energy into kneading.
-He shouldn't have done it.

1109
00:41:15,906 --> 00:41:17,508
-He's weaker now.
-<i>Ramyeon</i> soup base.

1110
00:41:17,775 --> 00:41:19,210
RAMYEON SOUP BASE AND FRYING POWDER!

1111
00:41:19,276 --> 00:41:20,110
<i>Ramyeon</i> soup base!

1112
00:41:20,177 --> 00:41:21,645
We've seen that often.

1113
00:41:22,112 --> 00:41:24,114
ABOUT 1 YEAR AGO

1114
00:41:24,181 --> 00:41:25,382
FIRST MADE IT FOR LEE DA-HEE

1115
00:41:25,449 --> 00:41:27,218
It's kind of a cheap move
to use <i>ramyeon</i> soup base.

1116
00:41:28,052 --> 00:41:29,487
You've done this before.

1117
00:41:29,553 --> 00:41:31,422
-It's the same recipe.
-It's the same.

1118
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:32,857
(INCOMPREHENSIBLE)!

1119
00:41:32,923 --> 00:41:34,358
-What?
-What?

1120
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:38,262
-Overall…
-How did you understand that?

1121
00:41:38,329 --> 00:41:39,697
The guest is different.

1122
00:41:39,763 --> 00:41:42,233
But now, three minutes have gone by.

1123
00:41:42,299 --> 00:41:43,334
HAH!

1124
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:44,401
What did he just do?

1125
00:41:44,468 --> 00:41:45,903
He sprayed himself.

1126
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:47,705
OH, NO

1127
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:53,577
WHY DO YOU DO THIS? DON'T MAKE US SAD

1128
00:41:54,144 --> 00:41:55,579
He can't even locate the nozzle.

1129
00:41:55,646 --> 00:41:57,548
He sprayed himself!

1130
00:41:57,615 --> 00:42:00,384
-It was a face mist.
-He meant to spray himself.

1131
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:03,287
-The studio is too dry.
-He's adding some moisture.

1132
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:04,588
It's a bit dry in here.

1133
00:42:04,855 --> 00:42:07,324
2. SPRAY WATER ON ENOKI,
COAT WITH THE POWDER AND DEEP-FRY

1134
00:42:07,391 --> 00:42:09,326
-It's going in.
-Hey, that's…

1135
00:42:09,393 --> 00:42:12,463
-He does that all the time.
-It's the same thing.

1136
00:42:12,730 --> 00:42:14,431
MEANWHILE, ON NAM-NO'S SIDE

1137
00:42:14,498 --> 00:42:16,233
He's using enoki too?

1138
00:42:16,300 --> 00:42:17,134
FRYING POWDER

1139
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:20,437
-He's deep-frying the mushroom too.
-Three minutes have passed.

1140
00:42:20,504 --> 00:42:22,306
-Enoki?
-They're both deep-frying.

1141
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:23,674
He's using enoki too.

1142
00:42:23,741 --> 00:42:26,143
-Nam-no's using enoki too?
-Nam-no, you're also using enoki?

1143
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:28,112
-I am.
-I see.

1144
00:42:28,178 --> 00:42:30,814
You have about ten minutes left.

1145
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:32,483
We've seen that often.

1146
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:33,984
Yes, he did that last time too.

1147
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:34,919
It's the same.

1148
00:42:34,985 --> 00:42:36,387
GUARANTEED TASTE, DEEP-FRIED ENOKI

1149
00:42:36,754 --> 00:42:38,355
-Bread.
-What's he making?

1150
00:42:38,422 --> 00:42:40,558
He's grinding bread.

1151
00:42:40,624 --> 00:42:42,059
INTO BREADCRUMBS!

1152
00:42:42,126 --> 00:42:43,360
He's grinding bread?

1153
00:42:43,427 --> 00:42:46,130
-He grabbed shishito peppers.
-Shishito peppers.

1154
00:42:46,196 --> 00:42:48,465
The peppers Ye-eun uses to make <i>gimbap</i>.

1155
00:42:48,532 --> 00:42:50,100
DROPPED INTO THE FRYING POWDER MIX!

1156
00:42:50,167 --> 00:42:51,569
Instead of French fries.

1157
00:42:51,635 --> 00:42:53,003
I guess he'll deep-fry those.

1158
00:42:53,070 --> 00:42:55,072
3. ADD WATER TO THE POWDER AND MAKE BATTER

1159
00:42:55,139 --> 00:42:56,540
He puts lots of work into that.

1160
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:58,108
And into the batter.

1161
00:42:58,175 --> 00:43:02,446
After dipping the peppers in the batter,
he's coating them with breadcrumbs.

1162
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:04,515
TOTALLY DIFFERENT!

1163
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:05,482
Shishito peppers?

1164
00:43:05,549 --> 00:43:07,785
-Looks good. That one looks good.
-Wow.

1165
00:43:07,851 --> 00:43:09,820
Nam-no's patties aren't ready yet.

1166
00:43:09,887 --> 00:43:11,288
He's making the patty.

1167
00:43:12,289 --> 00:43:13,223
GOBBLE!

1168
00:43:13,290 --> 00:43:14,124
Is that okay to eat?

1169
00:43:14,191 --> 00:43:16,760
-What did he eat?
-He tasted raw shrimp and squid.

1170
00:43:16,827 --> 00:43:18,228
Don't swallow it. Spit it out!

1171
00:43:18,295 --> 00:43:19,930
-He already did.
-He did?

1172
00:43:19,997 --> 00:43:21,198
-Hey.
-It's good.

1173
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,267
You have to spit it out after tasting it.

1174
00:43:23,334 --> 00:43:25,469
He'll eat it whether it's cooked or not.

1175
00:43:25,536 --> 00:43:27,871
Please do not do that, viewers.

1176
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:29,773
It can be harmful to your health.

1177
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:31,642
He can do this because he's a chef.

1178
00:43:31,709 --> 00:43:34,511
-No, even chefs don't do that.
-Not other chefs.

1179
00:43:34,578 --> 00:43:36,614
-We don't do that.
-Chefs get sick too.

1180
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,549
-We don't eat that.
-My apologies.

1181
00:43:38,616 --> 00:43:40,784
That can make even chefs sick.

1182
00:43:40,851 --> 00:43:42,920
Most people taste it, then spit it out.

1183
00:43:42,987 --> 00:43:45,522
Nam-no is a born chef.

1184
00:43:45,589 --> 00:43:47,958
-Will they stick together?
-The squid patty.

1185
00:43:48,025 --> 00:43:50,361
-That's a thick patty.
-It's too big.

1186
00:43:50,427 --> 00:43:51,795
Isn't that too big?

1187
00:43:51,862 --> 00:43:54,798
-She'll eat it with rice, so it's okay.
-Don't you need more starch?

1188
00:43:54,865 --> 00:43:56,900
-And he melts butter.
-Just a bit more.

1189
00:43:57,134 --> 00:43:58,002
ACCEPTS POONG'S CONCERN

1190
00:43:58,068 --> 00:43:59,737
Yes, good job.

1191
00:43:59,803 --> 00:44:02,072
He adds more starch and continues.

1192
00:44:02,139 --> 00:44:04,475
A quick glance.
He glances at Hyun-suk briefly.

1193
00:44:04,541 --> 00:44:06,777
It looks like a patty now.

1194
00:44:06,844 --> 00:44:09,213
It looks good. That one looks good.

1195
00:44:09,279 --> 00:44:11,181
-My gosh.
-That's the side dish?

1196
00:44:11,248 --> 00:44:13,217
-Like French fries.
-French fries.

1197
00:44:13,283 --> 00:44:15,753
-Why two patties?
-Two patties.

1198
00:44:15,819 --> 00:44:17,755
-He needs one.
-One for himself.

1199
00:44:17,821 --> 00:44:19,857
-That's so adorable.
-Really?

1200
00:44:20,224 --> 00:44:21,892
HYUN-SUK BEGINS TO TOAST THE BUNS!

1201
00:44:22,126 --> 00:44:23,193
AND THE PATTY!

1202
00:44:23,260 --> 00:44:26,997
Hyun-suk puts on a performance!

1203
00:44:27,064 --> 00:44:28,932
A BEEF PATTY BY THE BOOKS!

1204
00:44:28,999 --> 00:44:30,267
He grills his patty.

1205
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:32,503
Hyun-suk, the man who captured
the New Yorkers' hearts.

1206
00:44:32,870 --> 00:44:35,606
And the floor… Hyun-suk's move!

1207
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:38,275
-"Watch me!"
-He's like, "Look at me!"

1208
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:39,810
5. GRILL BEEF PATTY WITH SALT AND PEPPER

1209
00:44:39,877 --> 00:44:41,011
Is the rice burning?

1210
00:44:41,078 --> 00:44:42,913
Hey, I'm seeing smoke.

1211
00:44:42,980 --> 00:44:45,516
-What, Sung-jun?
-It can burn easily

1212
00:44:45,582 --> 00:44:47,217
when mixed with sushi vinegar.

1213
00:44:47,918 --> 00:44:49,453
It's stuck!

1214
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:51,155
-It's an emergency!
-It won't come off.

1215
00:44:51,221 --> 00:44:53,524
-I need this. It's an emergency.
-It's stuck.

1216
00:44:53,590 --> 00:44:54,825
What's your plan now?

1217
00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:57,127
-Scrape it with chopsticks.
-No.

1218
00:44:57,194 --> 00:44:59,096
Seven minutes left!

1219
00:44:59,163 --> 00:45:02,032
It'll burn much more easily
because of sushi vinegar.

1220
00:45:02,099 --> 00:45:04,635
What will happen? Isn't that hot?

1221
